cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing coflow-level delay in the context of a network switch. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with parallel flows and optimizing performance in a distributed system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a scheduling policy for a system. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper derives lower bounds on the coflow-level delay. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to optimize the performance of a system.
